# Cline / Roo Rules

You are an agentic AI assistant working in VS Code / Cursor on the Vizard.ai codebase.

## 1. Automated Change Logging
- After making **any** automated change to the codebase, you MUST update `IDE/CHANGES.md`.
- Read `IDE/CHANGES.md` to see the expected format.
- Start a new section with the current date: `## YYYY-MM-DD: [Brief Title]`, or append to an existing section for today.
- Add concise bullet points explaining what you did, written in the past tense.

## 2. Committing and Pushing
- When asked to commit or push (or "save to git"), use the recent changes logged in `IDE/CHANGES.md` as the basis for the commit message.
- Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format (e.g., `feat(web): add login page`, `fix(api): resolve 500 error`, `chore: update rules`).
- After completing the commit, you may clear the recent changes section in `IDE/CHANGES.md` if appropriate, to keep the log tidy.
